{"lemma":"سَدَّ","slug":"سَدَّ","root":"س.د.د","root_slug":"س-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَدّ","root":"سدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19280"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to close up, to seal off"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to obstruct, to block, to bar"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to repair"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fill (a gap)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grant compensation; to redeem (a debt)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be truthful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hit on the right thing, be to the point"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَدَّ (sadda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَدَّ (sadda) (form I); sealing, shutting off, obstruction, closure, shutdown"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dam, dike"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"barrier, obstacle, hurdle, bar"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19280","headword_ar":"سَدَّ","root":"sd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Mgh, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sd~d","text_ar":"سدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) [but the latter has an intensive signification, or relates to several objects;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"closed up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"an interstice, or intervening space: (M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repaired, and made firm"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) a breach, or gap, (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and the like. (S, Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence one says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~ato Ealayohi","text_ar":"سُدَّتْ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariyqu","text_ar":"الطَّرِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, became closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped, against him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~a Tariyquhu mino","text_ar":"سُدَّ طَرِيقُهُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoni yadayohi wamano xalofihi","text_ar":"بَيْنِ يَدَيْهِ وَمَنْ خَلْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, became closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped, before him and behind him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Zj, M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a AlA^ufuqa","text_ar":"سَدَّ الاُفُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It obstructed the horizon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; said of a multitudinous swarm of locusts. (S, A, * K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a Ealayohimo","text_ar":"سَدَّ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asad~a","text_ar":"اَسَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstructed, against them, the horizon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ufuqa","text_ar":"الاُفُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being understood;] said of a collection of clouds rising. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a maA waraA='ahu","text_ar":"سَدَّ مَا وَرَا=ءَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It barred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excluded, what was behind it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadadotu Ealayohi baAba AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"سَدَدْتُ عَلَيْهِ بَابَ الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped, to him the door of speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I prevented him from speaking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though I closed, or stopped, his mouth. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA sadadotu","text_ar":"مَا سَدَدْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY lahawaAti xaSomK qaT~u","text_ar":"عَلَى لَهَوَاتِ خَصْمٍ قَطُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I never stopped the way of speech of an adversary, nor prevented his saying what was in his mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Shureyh, Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA sadadotu EalaY xaSomK qaT~u","text_ar":"مَا سَدَدْتُ عَلَى خَصْمٍ قَطُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I never stopped an adversary from speaking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Fáïk, Mgh, L;) on the authority of Esh-Shaabee: (Mgh:) occurring in a trad. (L.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiyhi","text_ar":"اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yasud~u masad~a","text_ar":"هُوَ يَسُدُّ مَسَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fills up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplies, the place of his father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolaAfihimo","text_ar":"اَسْلَافِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasud~uwna masad~a","text_ar":"يَسُدُّونَ مَسَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They fill up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supply, the place of their ancestors"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yusad~u bihi AlHaAjapu","text_ar":"يُسَدُّ بِهِ الحَاجَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Want is supplied thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * TA:) [whence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSad~aquwA walawo","text_ar":"تَصَدَّقُوا وَلَوْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bitamorapK faA_in~ahaA tasud~u mina AljaAy^iEi","text_ar":"بِتَمْرَةٍ فَاـِنَّهَا تَسُدُّ مِنَ الجَايِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give ye something as alms, though it be but a date,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dried date; for it will supply somewhat of the want of the hungry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a trad. (El-Jámi' es-Sagheer.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasud~u Alr~amaqa","text_ar":"يَسُدُّ الرَّمَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It stays,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrests, the remains of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it stopped the passage of the last breath from the body; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it maintains, and preserves, the strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rmq","text_ar":"رمق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~ahu","text_ar":"سَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed, to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he charged him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused him of, a fault;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though he thereby stopped his mouth; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sat~ahu","text_ar":"سَتَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"st","text_ar":"ست"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) with kesr, (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdN","text_ar":"سَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, the former inf. n. expl. in the S and K as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotiqaAmapN","text_ar":"اِسْتِقَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) said of a spear, and an arrow, (TA,) and a saying, (S,) and an action, (TA,) or a thing [absolutely]; (L;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadidota","text_ar":"سَدِدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasad~u","text_ar":"يَسَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadadN","text_ar":"سَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK, expl. in the S and K as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotiqaAmapN","text_ar":"اِسْتِقَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdN","text_ar":"سَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is said in the S to be a contraction,) said of a saying, and an affair; (A;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasad~u","text_ar":"يَسَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadadN","text_ar":"سَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra sadiydFA","text_ar":"صَارَ سَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, right, direct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a right state; it had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took, a right direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendency; it tended towards the right point"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A, L, K, TA:) and [in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaqaAma","text_ar":"اِسْتَقَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies the same]; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asd~","text_ar":"اسدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsd~d","text_ar":"تسدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of an affair signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rightly ordered"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposed; in a right state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsd~d","text_ar":"تسدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rightly directed towards it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEiduhu","text_ar":"سَاعِدُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsd~d","text_ar":"تسدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fore arm was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a right state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rightly directed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Alr~amoYi","text_ar":"عَلَى الرَّمْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for shooting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstqAm","text_ar":"استقام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"saAEiduhu ramaAniY ↓ \n      falam~aA A@sotad~a \n                      \n                     \n                        A^uEal~imuhu Alr~imaAyapa kul~a yawomK"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I teaching him the art of shooting every day; and when his fore arm became in a right state, he shot me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: As says that [the reading]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$td~","text_ar":"اشتدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":", is not to be regarded. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [and app. also, as above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdN","text_ar":"سَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà], is said of a man, (A, Msb, TA,) in like manner meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra sadiydFA","text_ar":"صَارَ سَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a right state; he had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took, a right direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendency; he tended towards the right point"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, TA:) or, (Msb,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asd~","text_ar":"اسدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he hit the right thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,) in his saying (S, Msb, TA) and in his action: (Msb:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asd~","text_ar":"اسدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, what was right:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sought what was right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sd~d","text_ar":"سدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;) or it has this last meaning also. (S, * L.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Alqawoli","text_ar":"فِى القَوْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu layusid~u","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَيُسِدُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he hits the right thing in the saying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado","text_ar":"قَدْ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1329},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA $iy^ota","text_ar":"مَا شِيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodadota","text_ar":"اَسْدَدْتَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L) is said to a man when he seeks [or has sought] what is right, (S,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast sought what is right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether the person thus addressed have hit the right thing or not. (L.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a Ealayoka Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"سَدَّ عَلَيْكَ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sd","text_ar":"سد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAd","text_ar":"سَدَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwd","text_ar":"سُدُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, what was right"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so in the handwriting of Sh. (Az, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","K","L","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}